Lagos State Government yesterday diverted vehicular traffic at PWD, Ikeja, for asphalt laying on the Rail Level Crossing. The diversion will end by 6am tomorrow. Commissioner for Transportation, Dr. Frederic Oladeinde said in a statement that the asphalting of the Level Crossing was necessary to ease traffic across the rail track in the Ikeja section. 		 			Blackouts: Excuses, excuses …		 		 		 			Obiano’s wife must be a Senator		 		 		 			Emefiele lists conditions for stable exchange rate		 		 Motorists from GRA are advised to make use of Oba Akinjobi Way to link Airport Underbridge and access Agege Motor Road, while motorists from Oshodi coming into the GRA, Ikeja, will be diverted to Airport Bridge or Adegbola Level Crossing, from where they proceed to their destinations. Oladeinde urged road users to comply with the traffic directions provided by the Traffic Enforcement Personnel, as well as road signals to minimise inconveniences during the rehabilitation works. “Lagos State Government is hereby appealing to residents of the State, especially motorists that ply the corridor to make use of the alternative routes provided to ease traffic flow, as the palliative work is aimed at achieving a seamless multi-modal transport system that is being envisaged for the state,” Oladeinde said.